WEBVTT

00:09.167 --> 00:10.867
Life--it's literally
all we have.

00:10.967 --> 00:11.900
But is it any good?

00:12.000 --> 00:13.267
I'm a reviewer,

00:13.367 --> 00:15.067
but I don't review food,

00:15.167 --> 00:16.100
books, or movies.

00:16.200 --> 00:18.000
I review life itself.

00:18.100 --> 00:19.600
[screams]

00:19.700 --> 00:21.533
[triumphant music]

00:21.633 --> 00:22.433
[parrot squawks]

00:22.533 --> 00:26.800
*

00:26.900 --> 00:28.033
Over here.

00:28.133 --> 00:32.233
*

00:34.033 --> 00:36.100
Hello,
and welcome to Review.

00:36.200 --> 00:38.200
I'm Forrest MacNeil,
still reviewing life experiences

00:38.300 --> 00:42.400
despite having a real rough go
of it lately.

00:42.500 --> 00:43.500
In case you missed it,
a viewer

00:43.600 --> 00:47.700
recently asked me to kill
someone, and...

00:47.800 --> 00:49.167
now, a man is dead.

00:49.267 --> 00:50.467
(A.J.)
But look on the bright side.

00:50.567 --> 00:51.300
You're not going to jail
for murder.

00:51.400 --> 00:53.400
Well,

00:53.500 --> 00:55.533
I wish that were a bright side
that I could look on,

00:55.633 --> 00:59.767
but I--I actually--I
may be going to jail for murder.

00:59.867 --> 01:02.800
Right now, I'm just out on bail,
awaiting trial, so...

01:02.900 --> 01:03.967
Well, okay.

01:04.067 --> 01:06.533
But look on
another bright side.

01:06.633 --> 01:10.900
Being out on bail means
you get to do more reviews.

01:11.067 --> 01:12.367
Oh, yeah.

01:12.467 --> 01:16.700
Our next review comes
from Nicole in Mansfield, Ohio.

01:16.800 --> 01:18.233
"My neighbor made herself
an outfit from a trash can

01:18.333 --> 01:21.067
"and mumbles
about the CIA all the time.

01:21.100 --> 01:24.267
"She seems really happy,
but it's hard to tell for sure.

01:24.367 --> 01:27.633
What's it like to believe
in a conspiracy theory?"

01:27.733 --> 01:29.133
Okay.

01:29.233 --> 01:34.067
What's it like to believe
in a conspiracy theory?

01:34.100 --> 01:35.633
All right.

01:35.733 --> 01:37.767
(Forrest voice-over)
My first step was to attend
a lecture

01:37.867 --> 01:40.333
by a controversial author.

01:40.433 --> 01:43.933
I was clearly entering a world
of fear, obsession,

01:44.067 --> 01:45.333
and probably madness.

01:45.433 --> 01:47.633
(man)
Airplane mode is a joke.

01:47.733 --> 01:49.433
It is a dangerous time

01:49.533 --> 01:54.200
because the Illuminati is
coming up with various methods

01:54.300 --> 01:58.200
to bring about
the Fourth Reich.

01:58.300 --> 01:59.467
Controlling the weather,

01:59.567 --> 02:04.367
detonating underwater nukes
to cause tsunamis.

02:04.467 --> 02:07.267
(Forrest voice-over)
Listening to this man
ascribe all the word's tragedies

02:07.367 --> 02:09.533
to a shadowy
underground network,

02:09.633 --> 02:13.567
I began to grasp the appeal
of believing in conspiracies.

02:13.667 --> 02:16.267
Perhaps it would be nice
to think that life's misfortunes

02:16.367 --> 02:17.067
aren't simply random,

02:17.100 --> 02:18.733
but are instead the work

02:18.833 --> 02:21.600
of a villain who can be
smoked out and defeated.

02:21.700 --> 02:28.233
Which brings us
to the Interdimensional Bigfoot.

02:28.333 --> 02:29.367
(Forrest)
I understand better than anyone

02:29.467 --> 02:32.900
that the randomness
of life can be scary.

02:33.067 --> 02:34.433
Thanks to this television show,

02:34.533 --> 02:37.733
my entire existence
is given over to random chance.

02:37.833 --> 02:40.167
Gina, from Toluca Lake
has a question.

02:40.267 --> 02:41.267
What would it be
like to kill a person?

02:41.367 --> 02:43.467
What's it
like to be a cult leader?

02:43.567 --> 02:45.733
What's it like
to be kicked in the balls?

02:45.833 --> 02:47.367
And when you really
think about it,

02:47.467 --> 02:48.933
things
haven't always gone so well.

02:49.067 --> 02:50.100
[gunfire]
Ah!

02:50.200 --> 02:52.233
I am infested with sea lice!

02:52.333 --> 02:56.100
[screaming]

02:56.200 --> 02:57.300
[gagging]

02:57.400 --> 02:58.700
I'm having a heart attack,
you guys.

02:58.800 --> 03:01.400
Ow!
[screaming]

03:01.500 --> 03:02.800
Maybe it would feel
better to believe

03:02.900 --> 03:05.667
that the difficult experiences
I've had on this show

03:05.767 --> 03:09.533
were not the product
of pure blind, random chance.

03:09.633 --> 03:10.867
Is there any reason
to think that something else

03:10.967 --> 03:13.067
might be going on?

03:13.133 --> 03:18.233
Well, let's find out.

03:18.333 --> 03:20.067
Mm-hmm.

03:24.667 --> 03:26.100
Wow.

03:26.200 --> 03:27.633
Yeah.

03:27.733 --> 03:30.667
That's a lot
of dangerous reviews, isn't it?

03:30.767 --> 03:32.267
Look at how many times
I've almost died.

03:32.367 --> 03:35.600
I mean, that's really
surprising to me.

03:35.700 --> 03:36.567
It's 11 times.

03:36.667 --> 03:37.600
I've almost died 11 times?

03:37.700 --> 03:39.267
Oh, my God.
It's so many.

03:39.367 --> 03:40.400
No, that's a lot
of times.

03:40.500 --> 03:42.167
That's a lot of times
to almost die.

03:42.267 --> 03:43.133
I'm looking at this,

03:43.233 --> 03:45.400
and I'm thinking to myself,

03:45.500 --> 03:46.333
"When you consider
all the dangerous things

03:46.433 --> 03:50.067
that I've been asked
to do...

03:53.400 --> 03:55.067
How can that be random?"

03:55.133 --> 03:58.500
[suspenseful music]

03:58.600 --> 03:59.733
Can that really be random?

03:59.833 --> 04:01.600
Maybe somebody's trying
to kill you.

04:01.700 --> 04:03.533
(Forrest voice-over)
The suggestion
was ridiculous and silly.

04:03.633 --> 04:05.067
- No, but...
- And yet...

04:05.100 --> 04:07.067
What is going on? I mean
that's an incredible list.

04:07.167 --> 04:11.733
[Tina sighs]

04:11.833 --> 04:13.833
(Josh)
I mean, like,
maybe it's just,

04:13.933 --> 04:16.433
like, cool stuff.

04:16.533 --> 04:18.833
Oh, somebody definitely
wants to kill you.

04:18.933 --> 04:21.100
That's a bummer.

04:21.200 --> 04:22.200
- Have a good one.
- We'll miss you.

04:22.300 --> 04:22.800
- Yeah.
- Don't do anything dangerous.

04:22.900 --> 04:25.600
[chuckles]

04:34.067 --> 04:35.667
Good night.

04:35.767 --> 04:40.533
I'm gonna go too.
Good night, Forrest.

04:40.633 --> 04:45.533
My producer, Grant, oversees
every aspect of this show,

04:45.633 --> 04:48.067
and he has assured me that
the Review selection process

04:48.167 --> 04:49.300
is totally random,

04:49.400 --> 04:52.833
but I'm starting
to wonder about that now.

04:52.933 --> 04:54.500
[suspenseful music]

04:54.600 --> 04:56.967
What if Grant has chosen
all of the assignments

04:57.067 --> 05:00.233
that have hurt me so much?

05:00.333 --> 05:01.433
I need to know if that's true.

05:01.533 --> 05:03.600
[jiggling doorknob]

05:08.233 --> 05:08.867
[grunts]

05:08.967 --> 05:12.100
[crash]

05:12.200 --> 05:14.367
Come on.

05:14.467 --> 05:17.933
*

05:18.067 --> 05:20.333
Well, you certainly learn a lot
about a person

05:20.433 --> 05:22.267
when you ransack their office.

05:22.367 --> 05:25.367
Grant takes three different
kinds of fish oil supplement.

05:25.467 --> 05:28.100
Seems like an awful lot
of fish oil.

05:28.200 --> 05:30.433
He also subscribes to a magazine
here that seems to be nothing

05:30.533 --> 05:33.100
but photos
of antiquated medical equipment.

05:33.200 --> 05:35.733
I think that's real weird,

05:35.833 --> 05:37.367
but this
is what really interests me.

05:37.467 --> 05:39.400
This is called
the "Submissions Master List."

05:39.500 --> 05:40.800
Now, this is a list of hundreds

05:40.900 --> 05:42.433
of Review topics that have been
sent in to the show.

05:42.533 --> 05:45.400
"What's it like to fall in love
with a snowman?"

05:45.500 --> 05:46.800
"What's it
like to name a dolphin?"

05:46.900 --> 05:51.333
Now, every single one that
I have done is circled here.

05:51.433 --> 05:52.700
I believe this is the document

05:52.800 --> 05:57.067
from which Grant chose all
of the reviews that I have done.

05:57.167 --> 05:58.800
This is the smoking gun.

05:58.900 --> 06:01.567
(Forrest voice-over)
But the more time
I spent looking into Review,

06:01.667 --> 06:04.133
the more questions I had.

06:04.233 --> 06:05.967
Okay.
Here's the problem.

06:06.067 --> 06:07.600
Grant choosing all the reviews
does not explain

06:07.700 --> 06:10.267
all the terrible things
that have happened to me.

06:10.367 --> 06:11.667
Look at this.

06:11.767 --> 06:12.900
"What's it like to spend a night
at a haunted house?"

06:13.067 --> 06:16.067
That got me stabbed
in the belly by an old lady.

06:16.100 --> 06:18.167
[screaming]

06:18.267 --> 06:20.267
Why did that happen?

06:20.367 --> 06:21.800
Or this, here.

06:21.900 --> 06:23.667
"What's it like to spend
an afternoon on a rowboat?"

06:23.767 --> 06:25.933
Like, that should've
been a delightful experience,

06:26.067 --> 06:26.667
but I fell asleep,

06:26.767 --> 06:28.100
and my oars disappeared.

06:28.200 --> 06:29.133
Where are the oars?

06:29.233 --> 06:32.400
So either I am
the unluckiest person

06:32.500 --> 06:33.933
in the world,

06:34.067 --> 06:38.567
or Grant is not just
choosing these reviews.

06:38.667 --> 06:42.067
What if he's orchestrating
everything?

06:42.167 --> 06:43.200
And I got another problem.

06:43.300 --> 06:47.300
When I was buried alive here
for 24 hours,

06:47.400 --> 06:48.367
I almost died
because Josh and Tina

06:48.467 --> 06:49.733
forgot where they buried me.

06:49.833 --> 06:52.100
How do you forget
where you buried a living man?

06:52.200 --> 06:54.400
I got to get out of here!

06:54.500 --> 06:56.933
They're in on it.

06:57.067 --> 06:59.233
And so is Lucille.

06:59.333 --> 07:02.067
Jesus [bleep] Christ.

07:02.167 --> 07:03.567
Holy [bleep].

07:03.667 --> 07:06.600
Jesus [bleep].

07:06.700 --> 07:09.233
Jesus [bleep] Christ!

07:09.333 --> 07:11.700
It's a conspiracy.

