Hi. I need a room.

07:16.167 --> 07:17.733
I need a quiet room
in the back, okay?

07:17.833 --> 07:21.067
Hey, if anybody calls,
I'm not here, you understand?

07:21.167 --> 07:22.833
(Forrest voice-over)
I could no longer
sleep in my office

07:22.933 --> 07:24.467
as there was glass everywhere,

07:24.567 --> 07:26.067
and I believed my coworkers

07:26.167 --> 07:29.267
were conspiring to kill me
on national television,

07:29.367 --> 07:31.800
so I holed up
in a remote roadside motel

07:31.900 --> 07:34.700
to carefully think things
through

07:34.800 --> 07:37.567
over a period
of several days and nights.

07:37.667 --> 07:39.933
Oh, God! Oh, God!
Oh, [bleep].

07:40.067 --> 07:42.067
Oh, [bleep].
Oh, [bleep].

07:42.133 --> 07:45.167
There. See that?
See, the fire extinguisher

07:45.267 --> 07:46.900
was just out of my reach, just
past where I could reach it,

07:47.067 --> 07:48.867
and then the house
burned down because of that.

07:48.967 --> 07:51.900
Was Grant able to see me
as a little person and figure

07:52.067 --> 07:53.200
out how high I could reach
and then go to my dad's house

07:53.300 --> 07:55.367
and say, "Okay, I'll put
the fire extinguisher right here

07:55.467 --> 07:57.300
"so his little hands

07:57.400 --> 07:59.833
can only reach that high
and not reach it"?

08:00.067 --> 08:00.733
And this is me.

08:00.833 --> 08:02.067
I'm sadder than that.

08:02.167 --> 08:05.300
What kind of a monster
would make my dad homeless

08:05.400 --> 08:08.300
for a television show?
That son of a bitch.

08:08.400 --> 08:11.067
(Forrest voice-over)
Grant was obviously
behind everything.

08:11.167 --> 08:15.767
Every bad thing
that happened was him.

08:15.867 --> 08:16.967
Of course, of course.

08:17.067 --> 08:18.767
(woman)
Forrest, I've often wondered.

08:18.867 --> 08:21.100
What would it be
like to kill a person?

08:21.200 --> 08:24.100
My question is what would it be
like to kill a person?

08:24.200 --> 08:25.533
[click]
To kill a person.

08:25.633 --> 08:28.433
(Forrest voice-over)
The truth
I now knew was so huge,

08:28.533 --> 08:30.100
I could not bear it alone.

08:30.200 --> 08:31.433
I would need to visit
my ex-wife, Suzanne,

08:31.533 --> 08:32.567
at her mother's house.

08:32.667 --> 08:35.167
I would need to get help.

08:35.267 --> 08:37.933
I haven't been to the bathroom
in 14 hours.

08:38.067 --> 08:40.167
Don't let anybody in the door.

08:40.267 --> 08:41.500
- Forrest, go away!
- Okay.

08:41.600 --> 08:44.067
I just--I have something
that I need to explain to you

08:44.133 --> 08:47.067
that's gonna change absolutely
everything, okay? Just please.

08:47.167 --> 08:52.933
Please, this is the last thing
I will ever ask of you.

08:53.067 --> 08:54.500
- What is all this?
- This is all gonna

08:54.600 --> 08:55.967
help you understand
what's happening, okay?

08:56.067 --> 08:58.167
- Great. Come on in.
- All right. There's a lot

08:58.267 --> 08:59.900
to walk you through here,
and all of it is important,

09:00.067 --> 09:01.433
and it's hard
to know where to start.

09:01.533 --> 09:03.367
The first clue that I had that
something was wrong was this.

09:03.467 --> 09:05.067
This is a list
of every single review

09:05.133 --> 09:06.567
that has ever been
sent in to the show,

09:06.667 --> 09:08.567
and all of the ones
that I've done are circled.

09:08.667 --> 09:10.067
Do you know who circled them?

09:10.133 --> 09:10.867
- Grant?
- Yes, exactly.

09:10.967 --> 09:13.100
He told me it was all random.

09:13.200 --> 09:14.267
Keep your voice down,
please.

09:14.367 --> 09:15.867
You're gonna wake
up Eric and my mom.

09:15.967 --> 09:18.333
(Forrest voice-over)
I laid out all of my evidence
to Suzanne.

09:18.433 --> 09:19.433
All the pain.

09:19.533 --> 09:21.067
My review of having
a perfect body, okay?

09:21.167 --> 09:22.333
Oh, [bleep].
What is this?

09:22.433 --> 09:23.933
And my penis has never been
the same since then.

09:24.067 --> 09:25.300
No. [bleep].
Is it still like that?

09:25.400 --> 09:27.100
I had the thing taken out,
but it's still weird.

09:27.200 --> 09:30.067
It's like there's too much skin
now 'cause the implant came out.

09:30.100 --> 09:31.667
Let me just show it to you
so you have a sense of--

09:31.767 --> 09:32.600
Move on!
I don't want to see it.

09:32.700 --> 09:33.967
Fine. All right.
Fine, fine, fine.

09:34.067 --> 09:35.067
I don't think that that was
any normal magic eight ball.

09:35.100 --> 09:36.933
I think Grant
was controlling it.

09:37.067 --> 09:38.767
- Okay.
- Why did a pillow fight

09:38.867 --> 09:40.367
have to become so violent?

09:40.467 --> 09:42.367
And it turned into
a [bleep] bloodbath.

09:42.467 --> 09:45.267
This was supposed
to be a show about life, okay?

09:45.367 --> 09:48.867
Grant turned it into a show
about death. My death.

09:48.967 --> 09:50.367
That's what's happening here.

09:50.467 --> 09:52.900
And so I'm gonna tell him
I have figured it out.

09:53.067 --> 09:53.967
This is not what I signed on
for, and I am out of here,

09:54.067 --> 09:56.933
and I'm going back to my wife
and my kid,

09:57.067 --> 09:57.967
and I'm going back
to my old life.

09:58.067 --> 09:59.833
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
Forrest,

10:00.067 --> 10:00.967
I think it's really simple.

10:01.067 --> 10:04.467
You signed on to
an insane television show,

10:04.567 --> 10:07.667
and then you constantly
put that show above your needs

10:07.767 --> 10:09.967
and the people
that you love.

10:10.067 --> 10:13.333
I'm just not seeing
this evil plan.

10:13.433 --> 10:17.333
The only person that you need
to be afraid of is yourself.

10:17.433 --> 10:19.167
Oh.
[scoffs]

10:19.267 --> 10:22.533
I'm gonna prove I'm right,
and then I'll be back!

10:22.633 --> 10:26.367
(Forrest voice-over)
If I was going to convince
Suzanne of my conspiracy theory,

10:26.467 --> 10:27.967
there was one more thing
I needed to know.

10:28.067 --> 10:31.933
Why? Why was Grant
trying to destroy me?

10:32.033 --> 10:34.900
What had I ever done to him?

10:35.000 --> 10:37.600
This question plunged me deeper
into the darkness

10:37.700 --> 10:42.067
where I made a shocking
and upsetting discovery.

10:42.167 --> 10:47.867
I've been doing some research
here on HTML, ww.google.com.

10:47.967 --> 10:49.333
There's no trace of Grant
anywhere on the internet

10:49.433 --> 10:51.567
prior to 1995.

10:51.667 --> 10:52.633
It's like he does not exist.

10:52.733 --> 10:55.433
Now, 1995 happens to be
the same year

10:55.533 --> 10:57.667
that this woman supposedly
married a Chinese guy

10:57.767 --> 11:00.633
and disappeared to Hong Kong.

11:00.733 --> 11:03.600
This is Gretchen Edelberg,
and she had a really big crush

11:03.700 --> 11:04.933
on Suzanne when we
were all in college together.

11:05.067 --> 11:06.867
You see where I'm going
with this?

11:06.967 --> 11:09.867
Gretchen, okay, Grant.

11:09.967 --> 11:10.567
Gretchen, Grant.

11:10.667 --> 11:13.733
Gruh, Gruh, Gruh.

11:13.833 --> 11:16.867
She didn't move to Hong Kong.

11:16.967 --> 11:18.267
She got a sex change.

11:18.367 --> 11:20.933
He loves Suzanne so much,
after all this time,

11:21.067 --> 11:22.933
that he's gone
completely crazy.

11:23.067 --> 11:25.200
Get out of here,
you son of a bitch!

11:25.300 --> 11:27.067
(Forrest voice-over)
Now that everything
finally made sense,

11:27.167 --> 11:28.933
it was time to confront
the monster in his lair.

11:29.067 --> 11:31.333
Of course
he's not gonna open that gate

11:31.433 --> 11:33.200
because he knows
that I know the truth,

11:33.300 --> 11:34.433
and he's too much
of a [bleep] coward.

11:34.533 --> 11:37.600
Hey, you're too much
of a [bleep] coward

11:37.700 --> 11:40.633
to look me in the eye--
oh, [bleep, bleep]!

11:40.733 --> 11:42.067
Oh, God.
All right.

11:42.167 --> 11:43.867
Come on.
Let's go.

11:43.967 --> 11:45.867
- You [bleep] monster.
- Forrest.

11:45.967 --> 11:46.800
I know everything now.
[bleep].

11:46.900 --> 11:49.900
- What a nice surprise.
- No.

11:50.067 --> 11:51.533
- The guy's will bring it in.
- Ah, [bleep].

11:51.633 --> 11:53.267
I've figured it all out,
and I'm quitting the show!

11:53.367 --> 11:55.233
Again?

11:55.333 --> 11:56.067
Everything you've tried
to hide from me

11:56.100 --> 11:58.067
is out in the open now.

11:58.167 --> 12:01.500
You've ruined my life
for the last time, Gretchen.

12:01.600 --> 12:03.533
You bitch.

12:03.633 --> 12:05.067
This should be good.

12:09.267 --> 12:10.533
(Forrest voice-over)
I wasted no time

12:10.633 --> 12:12.733
unleashing the full weight
of all my damning evidence.

12:12.833 --> 12:14.367
Feel the walls of deception

12:14.467 --> 12:16.933
that you've built up
around yourself crumbling.

12:17.067 --> 12:18.533
You're at your producer's
house. I'm Grant.

12:18.633 --> 12:20.867
- You remember who I am, right?
- [laughing] Oh, yeah.

12:20.967 --> 12:22.067
(Forrest voice-over)
I forced Grant

12:22.133 --> 12:24.167
to come face-to-face
with what I now knew.

12:24.267 --> 12:26.167
The submissions master list.

12:26.267 --> 12:30.133
I've seen how all the reviews
I've done are circled.

