So I could tell
the IT guys

12:41.367 --> 12:43.333
to avoid any duplicates
because that time

12:43.433 --> 12:44.433
that murder came up again,

12:44.533 --> 12:48.733
I felt like
we'd let you down.

12:48.833 --> 12:50.267
Liar.

12:50.367 --> 12:52.800
Are you telling me this wasn't
one of your paid assassins?

12:52.900 --> 12:54.067
Are you serious?

12:54.100 --> 12:55.133
- How about that?
- Nope.

12:55.233 --> 12:55.567
That one
of your paid assassins?

12:55.667 --> 12:57.633
No.

12:57.733 --> 12:58.700
'Cause I know you did this.

12:58.800 --> 13:00.433
What is this a drawing of?

13:00.533 --> 13:03.200
(Forrest voice-over)
Grant demonstrated
incredible cool under pressure,

13:03.300 --> 13:05.300
offering sensible sounding
explanations for everything,

13:05.400 --> 13:09.467
but I saved my most
explosive accusation for last.

13:09.567 --> 13:10.900
There's one more picture
I want to show you.

13:11.067 --> 13:12.900
- Oh, great.
- This is the one

13:13.067 --> 13:14.500
you really don't want to see.

13:14.600 --> 13:16.800
- Oh, I want to see it.
- Because it's an old picture.

13:16.900 --> 13:18.967
It's an old picture...

13:19.067 --> 13:19.467
Let's see it.

13:19.567 --> 13:21.833
Of you.

13:21.933 --> 13:23.400
You were so pretty.

13:23.500 --> 13:26.433
- Now, who is this?
- Ooh, you're good.

13:26.533 --> 13:28.400
Was I cropped
out of this picture?

13:28.500 --> 13:31.267
You're Gretchen, and you
turned yourself into Grant.

13:31.367 --> 13:35.067
You went from this to this
to this.

13:35.100 --> 13:38.467
(Forrest voice-over)
Finally, the sheer weight
of my evidence wore Grant down.

13:38.567 --> 13:41.067
Okay, fine.

13:41.167 --> 13:43.267
I'm gonna tell you
exactly what's going on.

13:43.367 --> 13:45.067
No more hiding anything.

13:45.100 --> 13:48.067
Now, have a seat.
It's my turn to talk.

13:48.133 --> 13:50.533
(Forrest voice-over)
What he said next completely
blew my mind.

13:50.633 --> 13:57.233
People are constantly asking
you to review dangerous things

13:57.333 --> 14:01.233
because they already know
what the easy stuff is like.

14:01.333 --> 14:03.500
They can do that themselves.

14:03.600 --> 14:06.667
Living on the edge like this,
things will go wrong.

14:06.767 --> 14:08.433
People will get hurt,
and that is part

14:08.533 --> 14:12.800
of what we need you to help
us understand about life.

14:12.900 --> 14:14.333
I need you!

14:14.433 --> 14:17.633
Why would I want you dead?

14:17.733 --> 14:21.167
You know what?

14:21.267 --> 14:24.267
Besides all that,
I like you,

14:24.367 --> 14:26.167
and I know
I don't always show it,

14:26.267 --> 14:29.400
but the fact
is I consider you a friend.

14:29.500 --> 14:31.433
(Forrest voice-over)
By the time
Grant put the final nail

14:31.533 --> 14:33.433
in the coffin
of my conspiracy theory

14:33.533 --> 14:36.600
by showing me a photo
of himself growing up as a boy

14:36.700 --> 14:41.067
in the delightfully named town
of Sandwich, Massachusetts,

14:41.100 --> 14:42.967
it was not necessary.

14:43.067 --> 14:43.900
Sandwich, Massachusetts.

14:44.067 --> 14:46.867
That's what they called it.

14:46.967 --> 14:48.900
You were always a boy?

14:49.067 --> 14:50.300
[sobbing]
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

14:50.400 --> 14:53.100
- I'm really sorry.
- It's gonna be all right.

14:53.200 --> 14:55.467
- What are you doing?
- It's okay.

14:55.567 --> 14:56.800
I'm just trying to hug you.

14:56.900 --> 14:59.633
Come here. Come here.

14:59.733 --> 15:00.833
I'm sorry.

15:00.933 --> 15:02.100
There we go.

15:02.200 --> 15:04.267
There we go.

15:04.367 --> 15:08.233
(Forrest voice-over)
Letting go of my conspiracy
theory was bittersweet.

15:08.333 --> 15:09.833
It's always nice to hear
that you're not the target

15:09.933 --> 15:12.067
of a murder plot,

15:12.167 --> 15:15.600
but I no longer had an easy
explanation for my miseries.

15:15.700 --> 15:17.833
As long
as I do this important work,

15:17.933 --> 15:18.900
I will suffer,

15:19.067 --> 15:22.500
and my old life
will remain in the past.

15:22.600 --> 15:25.600
But great men
have always made sacrifices,

15:25.700 --> 15:29.067
and I know that I, with the help
of my treasured viewers

15:29.167 --> 15:31.300
and making the world
a better place,

15:31.400 --> 15:33.667
one review at a time.

15:35.767 --> 15:40.767
People do sometimes conspire
and sometimes with bad intent,

15:40.867 --> 15:44.233
but to accuse anyone
of that on flimsy, outrageous,

15:44.333 --> 15:48.133
or bizarre evidence
is an act of great cruelty.

15:48.233 --> 15:53.067
So I would like to apologize
to my producer and best friend,

15:53.167 --> 15:54.200
Grant.

15:54.300 --> 15:56.733
I give believing
in a conspiracy theory

15:56.833 --> 16:01.200
half a star.

16:01.300 --> 16:03.267
A.J., do we have time
for one more review?

16:03.367 --> 16:05.767
- Yes.
- And what is that?

16:05.867 --> 16:09.467
This one comes from Miles
in Sandwich, Massachusetts.

16:09.567 --> 16:11.067
- Really?
- Uh-huh.

16:11.167 --> 16:12.200
- Huh.
- Hey, Forrest,

16:12.300 --> 16:17.233
what's it like to be hunted?

16:17.333 --> 16:19.733
What's it like to be...
hunted?

16:19.833 --> 16:22.400
Yeah.

16:29.467 --> 16:33.233
What's it like to, uh...

16:33.333 --> 16:34.967
what's it like
to be hunted?

16:40.767 --> 16:43.567
I know it's possible I'm just
having some residual paranoia

16:43.667 --> 16:45.133
from my conspiracy theory
experience,

16:45.233 --> 16:46.200
but what is it
like to be hunted?

16:46.300 --> 16:48.500
And the person
asking this question

16:48.600 --> 16:49.833
is from Grant's hometown.

16:49.933 --> 16:52.233
Lucille, what is the population
of Sandwich,

16:52.333 --> 16:53.633
Massachusetts, please?

16:53.733 --> 16:55.267
You probably
shouldn't be here,

16:55.367 --> 16:59.300
'cause your hunter
knows where you work.

16:59.400 --> 17:00.700
What hunter?

17:00.800 --> 17:05.167
Grant asked me to hire
a former Navy seal to hunt you.

17:05.267 --> 17:08.467
What? Why?
What do you mean?

17:08.567 --> 17:10.067
You never do anything
like that without me

17:10.167 --> 17:11.667
specifically asking you to
please do something like that.

17:11.767 --> 17:14.067
- What is going on right now?
- Grant thought it would be best

17:14.100 --> 17:16.533
if I hired him so you

17:16.633 --> 17:19.233
wouldn't know what he looked
like or anything about him.

17:19.333 --> 17:19.867
Hey, Mr. MacNeil,
do you want us to help you

17:19.967 --> 17:20.933
hide or something?

17:21.067 --> 17:22.900
Or if he gets you,

17:23.067 --> 17:24.833
do you want us to bury you
in that same spot?

17:24.933 --> 17:27.767
And follow-up question:
do you remember where that was?

17:27.867 --> 17:30.067
Oh, my God.

17:30.100 --> 17:31.567
It's all true.

17:31.667 --> 17:35.067
You goddamn bunch of jackals
are really trying to kill me.

17:35.133 --> 17:36.400
Well, listen to me.

17:36.500 --> 17:38.600
I survived on garbage
in the middle of the ocean.

17:38.700 --> 17:40.233
I scratched my way
out of the grave.

17:40.333 --> 17:41.567
You think you can kill me?

17:41.667 --> 17:43.067
Nothing can kill me!

17:43.167 --> 17:45.200
- I'm not afraid of anything!
- Oh, my God. There he is!

17:45.300 --> 17:48.433
Aah!
[laughter]

17:48.533 --> 17:50.900
You [bleep] monsters!

17:51.067 --> 17:52.767
I've got to get out of this hell
you made for me.

17:52.867 --> 17:55.167
I'm gonna
do it [bleep] right now!

17:55.267 --> 17:57.400
Those are my keys.

17:57.500 --> 18:00.667
[suspenseful music]

18:00.767 --> 18:08.500
*

18:12.467 --> 18:14.267
Suzanne, I know now for sure.

18:14.367 --> 18:15.667
The show
is definitely trying to kill me,

18:15.767 --> 18:17.867
and I'm leaving it for real,
for good,

18:17.967 --> 18:18.900
and I'm coming to get you,
okay?

18:19.067 --> 18:20.967
I will explain it
when I get there.

18:21.067 --> 18:25.067
Hey, no! No! No!

18:25.133 --> 18:33.067
*

18:37.733 --> 18:39.433
Okay.
Are we rolling?

18:39.533 --> 18:41.167
'Cause there he is.
There he is.

18:41.267 --> 18:42.467
That's Forrest in the car

18:42.567 --> 18:44.600
that he stole
from his executive assistant,

18:44.700 --> 18:46.400
Lucille,

18:46.500 --> 18:48.067
and he's now approaching
a cameraman

18:48.167 --> 18:49.433
who I positioned there
in the road,

18:49.533 --> 18:51.433
and hopefully, the cameraman
won't frighten him.

18:51.533 --> 18:52.633
He's maintaining his pace,

18:52.733 --> 18:56.667
and he didn't frighten him,
so we're good.

18:56.767 --> 18:58.300
Okay.
I have positioned myself here

18:58.400 --> 18:59.567
because I figured
this would be

18:59.667 --> 19:02.333
the likeliest route
to Suzanne's mother's house.

19:02.433 --> 19:04.767
Forrest had
a little crisis of faith.

19:04.867 --> 19:07.433
He--he ran away from the show
yet again,

19:07.533 --> 19:10.800
and hopefully, I'll be able
to talk him down,

19:10.900 --> 19:12.167
and let's see
if we can work this out.

19:12.267 --> 19:14.367
We usually do.
Hi, buddy.

19:14.467 --> 19:16.533
Get out of the road, Gretchen,
or I swear, I will mow you down!

19:16.633 --> 19:17.900
[laughs] Gretchen.
Okay. Calm down.

19:18.067 --> 19:19.100
Let's talk about this.

19:19.200 --> 19:20.633
No. Just move your [bleep] car.
I'm out of here.

19:20.733 --> 19:22.567
That's it. No more of this!
I'm out of here for good!

19:22.667 --> 19:23.467
Let's calm down.
Just take a breath.

19:23.567 --> 19:25.367
"What is it like
to be hunted?"

19:25.467 --> 19:26.433
Oh, come on.
It's a random system.

19:26.533 --> 19:27.900
Oh, bull[bleep].

19:28.067 --> 19:30.300
You hired somebody
to hunt me down!

19:30.400 --> 19:32.567
I think you might be wrong
about the details.

19:32.667 --> 19:34.300
Really? Sandwich,
Massachusetts, huh?

19:34.400 --> 19:35.667
Sandwich, Massachusetts.

19:35.767 --> 19:37.500
- Explain that.
- That is a coincidence.

19:37.600 --> 19:38.933
- I haven't been there in years.
- Oh, really?

19:39.067 --> 19:40.667
I don't know anybody
from there anymore,

19:40.767 --> 19:41.800
and no one
is trying to kill you.

19:41.900 --> 19:43.833
Just another coincidence.
You got to think

19:43.933 --> 19:45.067
I'm the stupidest [bleep] person
in the world!

19:45.133 --> 19:47.333
- I think you're brilliant!
- Oh, really?

19:47.433 --> 19:49.133
- Forrest MacNeil!
- Oh, my God.

19:49.233 --> 19:51.833
Oh, my God!
Oh, [bleep]!

19:51.933 --> 19:53.300
Oh!

19:53.400 --> 19:55.500
If I'm gonna die,
you're gonna die too!

19:55.600 --> 19:58.067
- It's a blowgun!
- It's a what?

19:58.167 --> 19:59.067
[gun clacks]

19:59.133 --> 20:01.333
- [screaming]
- Oh, no!

20:01.433 --> 20:03.700
- [bleep] [bleep]
- Oh, my God.

20:03.800 --> 20:07.333
(man)
Oh, no. [bleep]

20:07.433 --> 20:12.600
- Oh, [bleep].
- [bleep]

20:23.767 --> 20:27.200
And so it seems
that another season of Review

20:27.300 --> 20:29.733
must end with me,
A.J. Gibbs,

20:29.833 --> 20:33.800
giving you the sad news that
Forrest MacNeil has vanished,

20:33.900 --> 20:39.600
and this time, with our beloved
producer, Grant Grunderschmidt.

20:39.700 --> 20:41.000
I don't like to be sad,

20:41.100 --> 20:43.833
so I like to think they're
floating down that river,

20:43.933 --> 20:46.467
settling their differences
with one another.

20:46.567 --> 20:48.067
And if I'm right about that,

20:48.167 --> 20:51.133
I'm pretty sure Forrest
would give being hunted

20:51.233 --> 20:55.700
six stars.

20:55.800 --> 20:57.433
That's all the time we have.

20:57.533 --> 20:59.367
This is A.J. Gibbs saying,

20:59.467 --> 21:01.067
"Life,
you're already living it.

21:01.100 --> 21:03.267
Ain't it great?"

21:03.367 --> 21:05.100
So long.

21:09.200 --> 21:13.500
(man)
Extra cheese.

21:13.600 --> 21:14.800
This is a list of hundreds

21:14.900 --> 21:16.167
of review topics that have been
sent in to the show.

21:16.267 --> 21:17.567
"What's it like to shake hands
with an old person?"

21:17.667 --> 21:19.567
"What's it
like to see an elephant?"

21:19.667 --> 21:21.300
"What's it like to shop
for bathing suits?"

21:21.400 --> 21:22.600
"What's it like
to join a club?"

21:22.700 --> 21:24.100
"What's it like to have
a yellow house?"

21:24.200 --> 21:25.733
"What's it like
to sing all day?"

21:25.833 --> 21:26.867
"What's it like to wear
someone else's pants?"
